oductSpace/Symmetric.html#LinearMap.IsSymmetric.restrictScalars","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/Analysis/InnerProductSpace/Symmetric.lean#L132-L133","name":"LinearMap.IsSymmetric.restrict_invariant","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/Analysis/InnerProductSpace/Symmetric.html#LinearMap.IsSymmetric.restrict_invariant","doc":"If a symmetric operator preserves a submodule, its restriction to that submodule is\nsymmetric. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/Analysis/InnerProductSpace/Symmetric.lean#L122-L127","name":"LinearMap.IsSymmetric.coe_reApplyInnerSelf_apply","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/Analysis/InnerProductSpace/Symmetric.html#LinearMap.IsSymmetric.coe_reApplyInnerSelf_apply","doc":"For a symmetric operator `T`, the function `fun x ↦ ⟪T x, x⟫` is real-valued. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/Analysis/InnerProductSpace/Symmetric.lean#L104-L117","name":"LinearMap.IsSymmetric.continuous","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/Analysis/InnerProductSpace/Symmetric.html#LinearMap.IsSymmetric.continuous","doc":"The **Hellinger--Toeplitz theorem**: if a symmetric operator is defined on a complete space,\nthen it is automatically continuous. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/Analysis/InnerProductSpace/Symmetric.lean#L95-L99","name":"LinearMap.IsSymmetric.add","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/Analysis/InnerProductSpace/Symmetric.html#LinearMap.IsSymmetric.add","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/Analysis/InnerProductSpace/Symmetric.lean#L92-L92","name":"LinearMap.isSymmetric_id","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib